.TH CUTSEL 1 "March 2026" "cutsel @PACKAGE_VERSION@" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
cutsel \- command\-line access to X selections and the cutbuffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cutsel
.RB [ \-selection
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-cutbuffer
.IR number ]
.RB [ \-debug ]
.RB [ \-verbose ]
.B cut
.RI [ value ]
.br
.B cutsel
.RB [ \-selection
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-cutbuffer
.IR number ]
.RB [ \-debug ]
.RB [ \-verbose ]
.B sel
.RI [ value ]
.br
.B cutsel
.RB [ \-selection
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-debug ]
.RB [ \-verbose ]
.B targets
.br
.B cutsel
.RB [ \-selection
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-debug ]
.RB [ \-verbose ]
.B length
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cutsel
provides command\-line access to X selections and cutbuffers. It can read or
write the cutbuffer, get or set the selection value, list the targets
advertised by the current selection owner, and query the selection length.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.BI "cut " [value]
Without
.IR value ,
print the current content of the cutbuffer and exit.
With
.IR value ,
store it in the cutbuffer.
.TP
.BI "sel " [value]
Without
.IR value ,
print the current content of the selection and exit.
With
.IR value ,
own the selection with the given value. The process stays running
until the selection is claimed by another client.
.TP
.B targets
List the TARGETS advertised by the current selection owner. This shows
which formats the owner can convert the selection to.
.TP
.B length
Query the LENGTH of the current selection value (as advertised by
the selection owner).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-selection ", " \-select ", " \-sel ", " \-s " " \fIname\fR
Specify which selection to use. Default is CLIPBOARD.
.TP
.BR \-cutbuffer ", " \-cut ", " \-c " " \fInumber\fR
Specify which cutbuffer to use. Default is 0.
.TP
.BR \-debug ", " \-d
Print debugging information.
.TP
.BR \-verbose ", " \-v
Be more verbose.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage information and exit. Does not require an X display.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information and exit. Does not require an X display.
.SH EXAMPLES
Print the current clipboard content:
.PP
.RS
cutsel sel
.RE
.PP
Set the clipboard to a specific value:
.PP
.RS
cutsel sel "Hello, world"
.RE
.PP
Print the current cutbuffer content:
.PP
.RS
cutsel cut
.RE
.PP
List the targets offered by the current clipboard owner:
.PP
.RS
cutsel targets
.RE
.PP
Read the PRIMARY selection instead of CLIPBOARD:
.PP
.RS
cutsel \-selection PRIMARY sel
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR autocutsel (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Originally written by Michael Witrant <mike@lepton.fr>.
